{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"610139c7-44db-481e-8d27-444aba2a8bf9","content":"Two key changes when moving to xUnit v3 with MTP:\n\n**1. `--filter` becomes `--filter-expression`** (MTP's flag).\n\n**2. Filter syntax changes.** VSTest used `FullyQualifiedName~IntegrationTests&Category=Smoke`. MTP uses a different expression language:\n\n```\n--filter-expression \"FullyQualifiedName~IntegrationTests and Category=Smoke\"\n```\n\nKey differences:\n| VSTest (`--filter`) | MTP (`--filter-expression`) |\n|---|---|\n| `&` | `and` |\n| `|` | `or` |\n| `~` (contains) | `~` (same) |\n| `=` (equals) | `=` (same) |\n\n**Your translated CI command:**\n\n```bash\ndotnet test --filter-expression \"FullyQualifiedName~IntegrationTests and Category=Smoke\"\n```\n\n`Category` works because xUnit v3 maps `[Trait(\"Category\", \"Smoke\")]` to MTP's `Category` property automatically. The `~` (contains) and `=` operators carry over; only the boolean operator and CLI flag name change.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"c1175a03-d755-435c-858d-51de5d78a951","outputTokens":283,"requestId":"A02F:252559:180D642:1B30BF3:69FE873B"},"id":"cd5104b8-352f-4800-add7-7dfd8c593961","timestamp":"2026-05-09T01:00:51.541Z","parentId":"c5374604-e615-4a21-9018-847ec95ac8d8"}
